    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m honestly so sad to let this beauty go, but it\u2019s time for a new home. This car is in absolutely pristine, mint condition\u2014I\u2019ve babied it since day one! It drives like a total dream and looks just like it did the day it rolled off the showroom floor. You seriously won't find a single scratch or hiccup here. If you're looking for a ride that\u2019s been loved and meticulously maintained, this is the one for you! Feel free to reach out if you have any questions or want to come take a look!",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This investment-grade E46 M3 represents a pinnacle of naturally aspirated engineering, featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant with six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. The high-revving mill is mated to a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock, ensuring precise torque vectoring. This example boasts a documented subframe reinforcement and proactive rod bearing service, addressing critical longitudinal chassis stress points. The suspension retains its factory-spec McPherson strut and multi-link geometry, providing the iconic 50/50 weight distribution and tactile feedback expected of a concours-level specimen. Finished in impeccable Carbon Black Metallic with zero paint depth variance, this chassis is mechanically and aesthetically flawless, free of any thermal cycling fatigue or fluid seepage.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
